Data Dictionary

  • referrer: referrer website/search engine
  • device: device used to visit the website
  • bouncers: whether a visit bounced (exited from landing page)
  • duration: time spent on the website (in seconds)
  • purchase: whether visitor purchased
  • n_visit: number of visits
  • n_pages: number of pages visited/browsed

Arrange



Top 2 Referrers by Orders

ecom %>%
  count(referrer, purchase) %>%
  filter(purchase) %>%
  arrange(desc(n)) %>%
  top_n(n = 2)
## Selecting by n
## # A tibble: 2 x 3
##   referrer purchase     n
##   <fct>    <lgl>    <int>
## 1 direct   TRUE        25
## 2 yahoo    TRUE        22

Case When

ecom %>%
  mutate(
    repeat_visit = case_when(
      n_visit > 0 ~ TRUE,
      TRUE ~ FALSE
    )
  ) %>%
  select(n_visit, repeat_visit) 
## # A tibble: 1,000 x 2
##    n_visit repeat_visit
##      <dbl> <lgl>       
##  1      10 TRUE        
##  2       9 TRUE

##  5       9 TRUE
